version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000016 - The Photon operating system must enable the auditd service.
global_description: |-
  Without the capability to generate audit records, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one. To that end, the auditd service must be configured to start automatically and be running at all times.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000016
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000039-GPOS-00017
  cci:
    - CCI-000132
    - CCI-000133
    - CCI-000134
    - CCI-000135
    - CCI-000169
    - CCI-001487
    - CCI-003938
  nist:
    - AU-12 a
    - AU-3 (1)
    - AU-3 c
    - AU-3 d
    - AU-3 e
    - AU-3 f
    - CM-5 (1) (b)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must enable the auditd service.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000016
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify auditd is enabled and running:

      # systemctl status auditd --no-pager

      If the service is not enabled and running, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Without the capability to generate audit records, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one. To that end, the auditd service must be configured to start automatically and be running at all times.
    remediation: |-
      At the command line, run the following commands:

      # systemctl enable auditd
      # systemctl start auditd
